observations.recommendation:
1. The Inventory Committee prioritizes the compliance with COA Circular No. 2020-006 for the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts to resolve the issues on unreconciled inventory balances;
2. The Municipal Treasurer maintains property cards for each class of PPE item; and
3. The Municipal Treasurer adopts and assigns the required property numbers and provide property tags/stickers for each PPE.

4. The Municipal Accountant prepares separate subsidiary ledgers for each road component and LRN Ledger Cards for each local road;
5. The Municipal Accountant presents in the Notes to Financial Statements the required disclosures pertaining to the road network system;
6. The Municipal Treasurer in coordination with the other members of the Inventory Committee, prepare and maintain a Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System and the Road Map;
7. The Municipal Treasurer keeps a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components; and
8. The Municipal Engineer provides assistance to the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer in determining the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

We recommended and Management, through the Municipal Accountant, agreed to:
Prepare separate subsidiary ledgers for each road component and LRN Ledger Cards for each local road;
Present in the Notes to Financial Statements the required disclosures pertaining to the road network system;
We also recommended and Management, through the Municipal Treasurer, agreed to:
In coordination with the other members of the Inventory Committee, prepare and maintain a Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System and the Road Map;
Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components; and
We further recommended and Management, through the Municipal Engineer, agreed to:
Provide assistance to the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer in determining the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

We recommended the following measures:
a. Requisition of fuel shall only be allowed by Management upon submission of duly accomplished/approved Requisition and Issuance Slip, and serially numbered/properly filled-up/approved Driver’s Trip Tickets;
b. Designated personnel to process the Monthly Reports of Fuel Consumption and Official Travels should ensure use of correct format and inclusion of all necessary information, and make available to the auditor for verification purposes.

